</head>

<body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h2>Terms & Conditions for Writers</h2>
        <p>Welcome to Imaginary Hub’s Writer Program! Before you start contributing your unique voice to our platform,
            please read through our terms and conditions carefully:</p>

        <h3>Content Guidelines</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Originality:</strong> All submissions must be 100% original and created by the writer.
                Plagiarism is strictly prohibited.</li>
            <li><strong>Topic Relevance:</strong> Articles should align with one of our content categories: Technology,
                Finance, Business, Education, or Human Psychology.</li>
            <li><strong>Quality Standards:</strong> Submissions should be well-researched, insightful, and free from
                grammatical errors. Each piece should add genuine value to our readers.</li>
            <li><strong>Word Count:</strong> The minimum word count for any submission is 800 words, with no maximum
                limit. However, ensure the content is concise and clear.</li>
            <li><strong>Community Guidelines:</strong> Writers must adhere to our community guidelines, promoting
                respectful, inclusive discussions. Offensive or harmful content is not tolerated.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Monetization Principles</h3>
        <p>We believe in rewarding our writers for their contributions. Here’s how our monetization system works:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Revenue Sharing:</strong> Writers earn a percentage of revenue based on article engagement
                (views, shares, comments). Higher engagement means higher earnings.</li>
            <li><strong>Subscription Model:</strong> Premium articles are available to subscribed readers. Writers
                receive a portion of the subscription revenue based on the readership of their articles.</li>
            <li><strong>Sponsorships:</strong> Writers may have the opportunity to include sponsor mentions in their
                articles. In such cases, revenue is shared between the platform and the writer.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Content Ownership</h3>
        <p>By submitting your content, you grant Imaginary Hub the right to publish, distribute, and promote your
            articles across all platforms. Writers retain the intellectual property rights to their work and can request
            removal or withdrawal of content at any time.</p>

        <div class="form-check mb-3">
            <input class="form-check-input accept-checkbox" type="checkbox" id="acceptCheckbox" required>
            <label class="form-check-label checkbox-label" for="acceptCheckbox">
                I accept the terms and conditions for writers
            </label>
            <div class="error-message" id="errorMessage">You must accept the terms and conditions to proceed.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="nav-right">
            <button type="button" class="button-dark small" id="agreeButton">I agree</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer mt-5">
        <p>&copy; 2024 Imaginary Hub. All rights reserved. <a href="/views/privacy-policy.html">Privacy Policy</a></p>
    </div>

    <script>
       document.getElementById('agreeButton').addEventListener('click', async function (event) {
    var checkbox = document.getElementById('acceptCheckbox');
    var errorMessage = document.getElementById('errorMessage');
    
    if (!checkbox.checked) {
        event.preventDefault(); // Prevent any form of navigation
        errorMessage.style.display = 'block'; // Show error message
    } else {
        errorMessage.style.display = 'none'; // Hide any previously shown error messages
        
        try {
            const req = await fetch("/terms", {
                method: 'POST',
                headers: {
                    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
                },
                body: JSON.stringify({ message: true })
            });

            let resp = await req.json();
            if (resp.message) {
                window.location.href = "/profile-creation"; // Use href to redirect
            } else {
                alert("Please try again");
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.error("An error occurred:", error);
            alert("An unexpected error occurred. Please try again later.");
        }
    }
});

    </script>

</body>

